<p class="lead">These are the recorded dedicatory instruments that govern Village at Ledge Stone. They are posted here for members and residents in accordance with the Association's obligations under the Texas Uniform Condominium Act (Tex. Prop. Code ch. 82).</p>

<div class="callout statute">
  <p style="margin:0"><span class="k">Which version controls.</span> The <strong>recorded instrument</strong> filed in the Official Public Records of <strong>Hays County, Texas</strong> is the authoritative version. The reading copies below are unofficial convenience transcriptions; if a reading copy and the recorded instrument differ, the <strong>recorded instrument controls</strong>. Every entry links to the county record so you can verify against the source.</p>
</div>

<h2>How these documents fit together</h2>
<p>Village at Ledge Stone sits inside a larger master-planned community. Two layers of covenants apply:</p>
<ul>
  <li>The <strong>Master Covenant</strong> is community-wide and is administered by the master (property owners) association. In that instrument, "Property" does <em>not</em> include the condominium.</li>
  <li>The <strong>Condominium Declaration</strong> creates the condominium regime and binds every unit here. It is administered by this Association, together with the recorded <strong>Community Manual</strong> (which contains the Certificate of Formation, Bylaws, Rules &amp; Regulations, and the Assessment Collection Policy) and the <strong>Design Guidelines</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="note">Each instrument's own Definitions article controls what its capitalized terms mean. The same word can mean different things in the Master Covenant and in the Declaration.</p>

{% macro instList(group) %}
<ul class="instruments">
  {%- for inst in instruments %}{% if inst.group == group %}
  <li>
    <span class="inst-title">{{ inst.id }} — {{ inst.title }}</span>
    <span class="inst-cite">Doc. No. {{ inst.docNo }}{% if inst.opr != "—" %} · {{ inst.opr }}{% endif %} · Official Public Records, Hays County, Texas</span>
    <span class="inst-summary">{{ inst.summary }}</span>
    <span class="inst-actions">
      {% if inst.reading %}<a class="btn small" href="{{ inst.reading }}">Read online</a>{% endif %}
      <a class="btn small ghost" href="{{ inst.pdf }}">Recorded PDF</a>
      <a class="btn small ghost" href="{{ inst.county }}" rel="noopener">County record ↗</a>
    </span>
  </li>
  {% endif %}{%- endfor %}
</ul>
{% endmacro %}

